==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: operant conditioning
<hw>op"er*ant con*di"tion*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Psychol.)</fld> <def>A process for causing animals to behave in a
specific manner by rewarding or punishing the animal each time it
performs a certain act; after a time, the animal comes to associate the
reward or punishment with the act, and will increase or decrease the
frequency of performing that act.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Operate</ent>⟦br⟧
